FIG. 1a is a simplified schematic perspective view of a paper coating operation utilizing a scanning reflectance-type infrared coating sensor according to the present invention;


FIG. 1b is an enlarged view of the uncoated portion of the sheet of FIG. 1a;


FIG. 1c is an enlarged view of the coated portion of the sheet of FIG. 1a;


FIG. 2 is a simplified schematic cross-sectional view of a detector assembly that includes the reflectance-type infrared coating sensor of FIG. 1a;


FIG. 3 illustrates an infrared absorption spectrum for the latex component of a typical sheet-coating material; and


FIGS. 4 and 5 are calibration curves for latex sensors vs. lab coat weight for different coat weights.

BWC =the basis weight of the coating material on the base sheet;


IMES =the value of the output signal from the measure detector;


IREF =the value of the output signal from the reference detector; and
